    "summary": "PhD in Social Sciences (Erasmus University), January 2021. PhD thesis: Living Apart Together. Rotterdam, Antwerp and Hamburg: relationships between port and city under pressure.\n\nRetired in 2020 as a lecturer at The Hague University of Applied Sciences.  Nowadays researching port and port city related issues, just to keep up with my PhD research activities. \nFrom july 2009 - 2020 full time lecturer at the Faculty Business, Finance and Marketing of The Hague University of Applied Sciences. Designing and teaching courses in Strategic Management, Marketing, Sales and Account Management. Lecturing courses and conducting workshops in assessing companies at the department of International Business .\nSpecialties: acquisition, product development, internal communication projects.\nDeveloping and teaching professional courses in Sales and Marketing.\nPersonal objectives were focussed on confronting students with the business reality.\nFrom 2004 to 2009 part time teaching marketing and sales at The Hague University, departments Marketing & Commerce, and Accounting and Financial management. \n\nFrom 1985 to 2009 involved in Marketing and Sales at Post NL (and its predecessors) and DHL: operations,, in- and external communications, sales and account management, new business and marketing; national and international. Community Investment strategies.",
